Ah, Korean food.

90
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:58,131
- Korean food?
<i>- Kimchi jjigae, doeniang jjigae…</i>

91
00:04:58,214 --> 00:04:59,424
- I like kimchi.
<i>- Kimchi jjim.</i>

92
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:00,550
<i>- Kimchi jjim?</i>
- Yeah.

93
00:05:00,633 --> 00:05:01,467
I like <i>kimchi jjim.</i>

94
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:04,262
Can I ask you something I'm curious about?

95
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:05,388
- About me?
- Yeah.

96
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:06,639
Okay, sure.

97
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:10,143
In Brazil, what's the…

98
00:05:11,436 --> 00:05:12,729
Uh…

99
00:05:13,229 --> 00:05:17,233
What's the dating scene like over there?
Do you do blind dates? Or…

100
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:18,443
Ah…

101
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:21,321
- We do blind dates, friends of friends.
- Oh yeah?

102
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:22,572
Yeah, friends in common.

103
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:24,282
- Friends of friends?
- Yeah.

104
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:26,743
- What about you?
- What?

105
00:05:26,826 --> 00:05:27,785
What?

106
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:29,412
Usually…

107
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:30,997
Like…

108
00:05:31,539 --> 00:05:32,999
- Have you dated before?
- Yeah, sure.

109
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:35,168
- Ever had a relationship? Ah.
- Of course I have!

110
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:36,627
You're 38?

111
00:05:36,711 --> 00:05:40,423
Thirty-eight. Yeah.
I'll be 40 pretty soon.

112
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:41,632
- Forty?
- Yeah.

113
00:05:41,716 --> 00:05:42,717
You…

114
00:05:44,218 --> 00:05:45,219
don't look like--

115
00:05:45,303 --> 00:05:46,346
Ah, thank you.

116
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:48,097
How many relationships? And when?

117
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:50,058
- Hm…
- Just curious.

118
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:51,809
Well…

119
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:55,605
- After I turned 20 years old.
- After you turned 20?

120
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,482
Yeah. After I turned 20.

121
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,901
Mm… Maybe…

122
00:06:02,695 --> 00:06:05,823
- Really?
- No. Just kidding. Um…

123
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:07,992
Five relationships.

124
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:09,369
- Five times?
- Yeah.

125
00:06:09,452 --> 00:06:11,788
Oh my God. That's a lot of relationships.

126
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:13,289
- You think so?
- Yeah.

127
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:15,917
I've had two relationships.

128
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,502
- Two.
- Yeah.

129
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:18,669
Uh, if it's okay…

130
00:06:19,962 --> 00:06:21,923
You know,
I'd love to see you one last time

131
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:24,217
before you have to leave for Brazil.

132
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:26,094
Okay, you can text me.

133
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:28,346
I'm not that into…

134
00:06:28,971 --> 00:06:31,140
uh… texting a lot.

135
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:33,768
In Brazil, I'm offline

136
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:35,978
- most of the time.
- Yeah. Yeah.

137
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:37,105
Because…

138
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:42,402
I'm not really into
spending a lot of time online.

139
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:46,030
But I use the internet a lot for chatting.

140
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:47,782
Well, I'll, um…

141
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:49,575
- text you.
- Okay.

142
00:06:49,659 --> 00:06:50,493
Yeah.

143
00:06:50,993 --> 00:06:52,328
So, um…

144
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:56,416
In Brazil, how do you guys say, "Bye-bye"?

145
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:57,333
Bye-bye?

146
00:06:57,417 --> 00:06:58,418
- In Brazil, yeah.
<i>- Tchau.</i>

147
00:06:58,501 --> 00:06:59,335
<i>Tchau?</i>

148
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,212
Yeah, that's what we say.

149
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:03,589
We say bye-bye like this, okay?

150
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:06,759
- Kiss here, kiss here. Okay?
- Yeah, okay.

151
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,594
The Brazilian way.

152
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:12,557
- And when this is goodbye and hello.
- Goodbye…

153
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:15,643
- Goodbye and hello. Oh, the same.
- The same. Yeah.

154
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:16,978
- Yes. Bye.
- Bye-bye.

155
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:18,604
- See you.
- See you. Bye-bye.

156
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:24,485
Bye-bye.

157
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:31,075
<i>I don't believe in happily ever after.</i>

158
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:35,246
<i>But I believe in</i>
<i>happy moments along the way.</i>

159
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:39,375
<i>Being at peace is</i>
<i>just as important as being happy.</i>

160
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:42,420
I've always tried to…

161
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,964
ignore my past,

162
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:47,717
but I think I did a good thing

163
00:07:49,260 --> 00:07:50,553
by getting this over with.

164
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:56,017
<i>When it comes down to it,</i>
<i>it's the journey that makes us who we are.</i>

165
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:57,810
<i>Not the final destination.</i>

166
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:15,745
I was going to wait
for Si-won to tell you this.

167
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:18,789
- Mm.
- But…

168
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:24,378
If…

169
00:08:25,379 --> 00:08:29,091
I have a daughter,
is that a problem for you?

170
00:08:34,388 --> 00:08:36,641
A daughter? I didn't know about that.

171
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,898
I don't mind it.

172
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:45,525
It's not a problem.

173
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:47,527
I'm not that kind of person.

174
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:49,529
I respect people.

175
00:08:50,071 --> 00:08:52,907
Life is so unpredictable.

176
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:55,451
Don't cry, Luanny.

177
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,411
These things happen, it's life.

178
00:08:58,371 --> 00:08:59,997
Isn't that right, Luanny?

179
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:00,998
Don't cry!

180
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:05,127
Let go of those… bad thoughts. It's okay.

181
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:07,338
I don't mind that.

182
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:09,423
I'm not that kind of person.

183
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:10,841
It's okay, don't cry.

184
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:14,720
I didn't know you had been
holding all that inside you.

185
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:15,846
Don't cry.

186
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,807
You'll mess up that pretty face of yours.

187
00:09:18,516 --> 00:09:20,518
I'm not that kind of person.

188
00:09:21,435 --> 00:09:23,312
I have a tissue here somewhere.

189
00:09:23,396 --> 00:09:25,606
Life is like this.

190
00:09:26,315 --> 00:09:30,194
Everyone has their own struggles.
This could happen to anyone.

191
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:32,572
Don't cry about it.

192
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:36,701
We want a good life for our children.

193
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:39,620
But parents shouldn't worry
so much about that.

194
00:09:39,704 --> 00:09:45,084
You just have to be a nice person and
have a good relationship with me, Luanny.

195
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:47,587
Not because we are in-laws now,

196
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:51,215
but to support each other
as a mother and as a daughter.

197
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:53,801
Helping each other whenever we need it.

198
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:57,013
Being present, giving love and affection.

199
00:09:57,096 --> 00:09:58,764
You know? Being together.

200
00:09:58,848 --> 00:10:00,349
That's the way I see things.

201
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:03,394
I don't care if you have money or not.
It's okay.

202
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:07,106
- Thank you, Mom.
- This is life. That's all. I don't mind.

203
00:10:07,648 --> 00:10:08,482
Not at all.

204
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:12,153
I was a little scared.

205
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:16,157
Because I know
our cultures are very different.

206
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,743
Very opposite, but…

207
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:23,831
I was feeling awful
because I was hiding something.

208
00:10:23,914 --> 00:10:26,125
I'm sorry I didn't tell you before.

209
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:28,252
It's okay.

210
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:29,712
Just be responsible.

211
00:10:29,795 --> 00:10:32,965
Take good care of your daughter…
of each other.

212
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:36,260
Help each other through difficult times.

213
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:39,305
The main goal is to have a good life.

214
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:42,850
Having a good, happy life. Isn't it?
Everything is fine.

215
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:46,687
The mood feels good.

216
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:49,357
We're getting along.

217
00:10:50,232 --> 00:10:51,984
Mom gave me this, look.

218
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:53,819
So, Mom.

219
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,655
What's your first impression?

220
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,031
She's so pretty!

221
00:10:57,114 --> 00:11:00,159
- Really? Sure about that?
- You have to be nice to her.

222
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:06,082
- Anyway, Mom.
- Mm?

223
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:11,045
There are some things I didn't tell you.

224
00:11:11,629 --> 00:11:13,923
I know. She's just told me.

225
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:15,758
- So you know?
- Yes.

226
00:11:15,841 --> 00:11:17,760
It's okay. I don't mind it.

227
00:11:18,427 --> 00:11:21,013
- It'll be good for you.
- I'm a… little bit scared.

228
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:26,394
Now there's a lovely child in our lives.
I'm really glad.

229
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:30,773
Loving your kids
shouldn't make you embarrassed.

230
00:11:30,856 --> 00:11:33,275
Children are a blessing. Don't you think?

231
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:36,570
You should be confident
and proud of your life.

232
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:38,572
- Luanny…
- Do your best.

233
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,492
Luanny, you…

234
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:43,703
Uh…

235
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:47,289
To be honest, I already had a feeling that

236
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:50,751
when you met my mom, she would understand.

237
00:11:51,460 --> 00:11:54,380
I had a feeling that this would happen.

238
00:11:55,339 --> 00:11:56,507
When you told her.

239
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:01,053
I'm happy everything's settled.

240
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,390
Thank you for accepting me, Mom.

241
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:08,728
I promise I'll take care of him
and knock some sense into his head.

242
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:14,275
And we'll come here to Korea
many times to visit you.

243
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,737
And I'll bring you
many things from Brazil.

244
00:12:18,237 --> 00:12:19,155
I promise.

245
00:12:19,697 --> 00:12:21,866
I'm not saying thank you.

246
00:12:22,742 --> 00:12:27,580
All I want is for you to get along well
from now on.

247
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:29,415
- Understand?
- We will.

248
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,084
And love each other.

249
00:12:32,168 --> 00:12:33,335
Shall we?

250
00:12:35,087 --> 00:12:36,088
Let's…

251
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:38,382
give Mom a hug.

252
00:12:42,303 --> 00:12:43,304
Let's go.

253
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:46,182
Careful.

254
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:51,896
<i>In fairytales, the princess</i>
<i>faces off with witches and dragons</i>

255
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:53,230
<i>to live with the prince.</i>

256
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:56,233
<i>My prince is not very… charming,</i>

257
00:12:56,317 --> 00:12:59,487
<i>and I know my story</i>
<i>is far from a fairytale.</i>

258
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:02,156
<i>But I still want to fight</i>
<i>for my happily ever after.</i>

259
00:13:02,239 --> 00:13:04,700
Do you have
