But thank you so much.

502
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:22,070
<i>Our trip may be coming to an end, but</i>

503
00:30:22,153 --> 00:30:24,697
<i>everything we experienced here…</i>

504
00:30:24,781 --> 00:30:26,866
<i>Ah, this will definitely</i>
<i>go down in history.</i>

505
00:30:26,950 --> 00:30:27,992
It's very well lit.

506
00:30:28,076 --> 00:30:30,745
Look at this vibe,
look at this view, guys.

507
00:30:31,579 --> 00:30:32,664
The moon.

508
00:30:33,289 --> 00:30:34,749
It's smiling at us today.

509
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:45,051
Hi!

510
00:30:45,134 --> 00:30:47,136
Luanny.

511
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:49,055
Camila!

512
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:53,268
music continues]

513
00:30:56,938 --> 00:30:59,899
Remember?
The first time I gave you flower.

514
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:09,951
Guys, what about there?

515
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:12,996
Wow, everyone!

516
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:14,998
Whoa!

517
00:31:20,044 --> 00:31:21,421
Let's all stand up.

518
00:31:23,214 --> 00:31:27,176
So I invited all girls
to be our bridesmaids.

519
00:31:27,260 --> 00:31:30,513
Yeah, so let's make cheers.

520
00:31:30,597 --> 00:31:31,681
- It's good?
- Good!

521
00:31:31,764 --> 00:31:36,311
Cheers!

522
00:31:56,539 --> 00:31:59,959
It's good that you came
and you got to meet my friends.

523
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:02,045
All of them are very beautiful,

524
00:32:02,128 --> 00:32:03,046
but Katy is…

525
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:05,548
the most beautiful.

526
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:07,300
I'm always the prettiest.

527
00:32:08,593 --> 00:32:10,803
I have to tell you something.

528
00:32:10,887 --> 00:32:12,597
I went to meet my mother-in-law.

529
00:32:13,306 --> 00:32:14,682
And then? Did you?

530
00:32:15,433 --> 00:32:17,185
And then…

531
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:19,354
She said she has a new granddaughter now.

532
00:32:20,104 --> 00:32:21,689
- Oh my God!
- What?

533
00:32:21,773 --> 00:32:23,107
- How beautiful!
- You're kidding!

534
00:32:23,191 --> 00:32:24,943
And that she's very happy.

535
00:32:26,819 --> 00:32:27,737
Amazing!

536
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:35,036
And she said I didn't need to be afraid,
because having a child is not a problem.

537
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:37,497
- That's great! Halleluiah!
- That a child is a blessing.

538
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:39,082
And that she still loves me.

539
00:32:41,417 --> 00:32:44,504
That's good news. That's-That's… Wow!

540
00:32:44,587 --> 00:32:45,672
My God, Danny!

541
00:32:45,755 --> 00:32:47,423
Now, look!

542
00:32:48,716 --> 00:32:50,718
No, no.

543
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:52,887
Now you buy one for her.

544
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:53,846
Yes!

545
00:32:53,930 --> 00:32:55,056
- Yes, I will.
- Yeah!

546
00:32:55,139 --> 00:32:56,432
Can we get married now?

547
00:32:56,516 --> 00:32:57,850
Give me my ring.

548
00:32:58,893 --> 00:33:00,353
Yeah she wants now.

549
00:33:02,355 --> 00:33:04,357
We are so happy for you, babe.

550
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,692
I'm so happy too!

551
00:33:05,775 --> 00:33:09,237
Guys, I also have something to tell.

552
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:11,072
- Mm!
- We went to Namsan Tower.

553
00:33:11,155 --> 00:33:13,282
- Oh!
- For the first time.

554
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:18,121
Yeah, it's like a postal card of Korea.
So amazing, so beautiful, right?

555
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:23,793
And it's so romantic, the ambiance there,
and it was amazing, right?

556
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:24,919
Yes.

557
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,587
Do you kiss her? You kissed her?

558
00:33:27,714 --> 00:33:29,507
- The first kiss then?
- Oh…

559
00:33:29,590 --> 00:33:30,508
Y-yes!

560
00:33:32,635 --> 00:33:34,470
Danny! Danny! Danny!

561
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:38,349
Danny! Danny! Danny!

562
00:33:38,933 --> 00:33:40,059
Kiss again.

563
00:33:40,143 --> 00:33:41,644
No, no.

564
00:33:41,728 --> 00:33:43,438
- I want to see that.
- Let's dance!

565
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:45,815
Great idea.

566
00:33:51,821 --> 00:33:52,947
Do it like this.

567
00:34:05,543 --> 00:34:06,627
Are you okay?

568
00:34:08,838 --> 00:34:11,007
You made a wish when you came…

569
00:34:11,591 --> 00:34:12,884
A wish?

570
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:15,219
- Yeah.
- In Cheonggyecheon.

571
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:17,638
- Hmm?
- You tossed a coin, right?

572
00:34:20,725 --> 00:34:25,188
In Cheonggyecheon, I wished
for my friends to have a good time here.

573
00:34:26,939 --> 00:34:28,941
- Spend the time here?
- Mm?

574
00:34:29,734 --> 00:34:31,277
I wished for the girls…

575
00:34:32,278 --> 00:34:33,571
A good time here,

576
00:34:34,155 --> 00:34:37,408
and we go back to Brazil.

577
00:34:42,914 --> 00:34:44,123
I feel like crying.

578
00:34:44,207 --> 00:34:45,416
Oh, so sad.

579
00:34:47,794 --> 00:34:49,545
Weren't you crying just now?

580
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:51,089
I cried a lot.

581
00:34:51,672 --> 00:34:53,299
I don't usually cry.

582
00:34:58,221 --> 00:34:59,806
When you're in Brazil,

583
00:35:00,848 --> 00:35:01,933
DM me.

584
00:35:02,517 --> 00:35:04,435
- What?
- DM. Insta DM.

585
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:09,649
Oh…

586
00:35:19,992 --> 00:35:25,331
What if you meet someone
cooler than me? No?

587
00:35:27,792 --> 00:35:28,793
So sad.

588
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:35,341
You met a lot of people.

589
00:35:37,009 --> 00:35:41,597
Who are probably pretty similar.
And you're a good person.

590
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:43,349
- Me?
- Yeah.

591
00:35:43,432 --> 00:35:44,517
I'm crazy.

592
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,811
- Oh no!
- I'm a little crazy.

593
00:35:46,894 --> 00:35:47,979
Oh, a little?

594
00:35:48,646 --> 00:35:49,605
Uh-huh.

595
00:35:50,773 --> 00:35:54,610
When you go back to Brazil,
you'll remember your country, right?

596
00:35:57,029 --> 00:35:58,573
Will you remember me?

597
00:35:59,073 --> 00:36:00,366
- You?
- Yeah.

598
00:36:02,702 --> 00:36:06,789
I'm glad you came here, Camila,
and that I got to meet you.

599
00:36:15,298 --> 00:36:19,010
Have a safe trip back.
And let's keep in touch.

600
00:36:20,845 --> 00:36:22,847
Bye. Yeah.

601
00:36:22,930 --> 00:36:25,141
- Oh, this Braz-Brazil.
- Brazil way?

602
00:36:25,224 --> 00:36:26,350
- Yeah.
- Okay.

603
00:36:28,561 --> 00:36:29,562
Bye.

604
00:36:34,317 --> 00:36:38,946
<i>I came here to put an end</i>
<i>to a long chapter of my life.</i>

605
00:36:40,406 --> 00:36:44,452
<i>To start over,</i>
<i>some stories need to come to an end.</i>

606
00:36:44,535 --> 00:36:48,623
<i>And a new chapter doesn't always</i>
<i>have room for someone new.</i>

607
00:37:05,681 --> 00:37:09,393
Bring me that sparkly drink!
Twinkle, twinkle, babe!

608
00:37:30,581 --> 00:37:32,416
The worst part of the trip…

609
00:37:32,917 --> 00:37:33,793
Is leaving, right?

610
00:37:33,876 --> 00:37:35,253
…is when it's over.

611
00:37:35,336 --> 00:37:37,630
It went by so fast, right?

612
00:37:37,713 --> 00:37:39,048
But it was so intense.

613
00:37:39,131 --> 00:37:40,716
It was. What we experienced here--

614
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:44,387
Oh my God, my little duck.
A happy family reunited.

615
00:37:44,971 --> 00:37:47,848
- What does it mean? I never understood.
- I'm afraid of breaking it.

616
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:51,352
It's a symbol because
ducks never separate from each other.

617
00:37:51,852 --> 00:37:55,856
So, Su-woong and I will never split up.

618
00:37:56,649 --> 00:38:00,945
<i>We came to Korea to find out</i>
<i>if K-dramas exist in real life.</i>

619
00:38:02,613 --> 00:38:04,865
<i>I'm sure that they do.</i>

620
00:38:06,909 --> 00:38:09,870
<i>I prefer to tell my story another way.</i>

621
00:38:12,623 --> 00:38:14,917
<i>For me, it's a mix of different things.</i>

622
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:17,545
I'm going to miss that too.

623
00:38:17,628 --> 00:38:18,671
Waking up, Morena,

624
00:38:18,754 --> 00:38:21,632
and you being there at the counter
already waiting for me with coffee.

625
00:38:21,716 --> 00:38:22,591
Oh, okay.

626
00:38:22,675 --> 00:38:25,386
- So we can gossip about life.
- Wow, this is so heavy.

627
00:38:25,469 --> 00:38:26,762
Damn, the suitcase is heavy.

628
00:38:26,846 --> 00:38:28,264
It wasn't like that, huh?

629
00:38:28,347 --> 00:38:30,975
- What's in there? It wasn't like that.
- Let me put the bag here.

630
00:38:31,058 --> 00:38:32,351
Hey, Luanny!

631
00:38:32,977 --> 00:38:34,395
Let's go. The car is here.

632
00:38:34,478 --> 00:38:36,105
Let's go, Lu.

633
00:38:36,689 --> 00:38:37,815
I'm not going with you guys.

634
00:38:37,898 --> 00:38:39,108
What?

635
00:38:39,608 --> 00:38:42,820
Si-won is picking me up. I'm going
to spend more time here in Korea.

636
00:38:45,406 --> 00:38:47,074
- Why?
- Are you serious?

637
00:38:47,158 --> 00:38:50,911
After I met his mom, I wanted to learn
more about his family and about him.

638
00:38:51,787 --> 00:38:53,456
I think I'll stay a little longer.

639
00:38:53,539 --> 00:38:55,124
Oh my God! I'm gonna miss you.

640
00:38:55,207 --> 00:38:56,167
Give me a hug!

641
00:38:56,250 --> 00:38:58,377
Group hug. Everyone together!

642
00:39:04,175 --> 00:39:05,885
Guys, let's go, or we'll miss the car.

643
00:39:05,968 --> 00:39:09,055
Yeah, we'll miss
the car, the flight, everything.

644
00:39:09,138 --> 00:39:12,767
- You better text us, okay?
- Yeah, send us a message. Bye, Lu.

645
00:39:13,267 --> 00:39:16,312
- Send us a text. God bless.
- Thank you for this experience.

646
00:39:20,733 --> 00:39:24,153
<i>With or without a K-drama,</i>
<i>I believe in love.</i>

647
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:31,410
THREE MONTHS LATER

648
00:39:35,122 --> 00:39:37,708
BELO HORIZONTE, BRAZIL
